# Portal feature (CRUD)

**Canonical reference:** `portal/admin/features/vehicles/` — follow this layout for new admin list + create + edit features.

User features follow the same `data/` / `form/` layout — reference: `portal/user/features/transport/`. User list features split **All** vs **My** into sibling folders `table-all/` and `table-our/` (separate table defs + page components per scope).

## Folder layout

```
features/<entity>/
  data/
    ...
  form/
    ...
  table/                     # admin (single list)
    <entity>.table.ts
    <entity>-table-page.component.{ts,html,scss}
  table-all/                 # user — external company items
    <entity>-all.table.ts
    <entity>-all-table-page.component.{ts,html,scss}
  table-our/                  # user — session company items
    <entity>-my.table.ts
    <entity>-my-table-page.component.{ts,html,scss}
```

## data/

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `*.model.ts` | `EntityFormModel` interface; `Entity extends EntityFormModel` with `id`; union types for enums; **`status` on entity** (not form model unless editable) — see `entity-status.mdc` |
| `*.constants.ts` | `ADMIN_<ENTITY>_API` (HTTP only — not app URLs); option arrays reused by form + table filters |
| `*.mock-data.ts` | `ENTITY_MOCK_DATA: Entity[]` |
| `*.service.ts` | `@Injectable({ providedIn: 'root' })`; in-memory `store` from mock; **`list()`** (admin) or **`listAll()` / `listOurs()`** (user) applies `TableQuery`; `getById`, `create`, `update`, `delete` with `delay()` until API; **`create()` default `status`**; **`update()` preserve `status`** — see `entity-status.mdc` |

Service naming: `AdminVehicleService` (portal prefix when helpful). Swap mock store for `HttpClient` later — keep the same method signatures.

## Routes + nav + URLs

1. **`shared/constants/admin-urls.ts`** or **`user-urls.ts`** — create URL, edit URL builder, hub URLs (user Plan 3); re-exported by `app-urls.ts` (see `app-urls.mdc`).
   - **User entities (Plan 3):** `USER_FIND_URL`, `USER_OUR_LISTINGS_URL`, `userFindUrl()` / `userOurListingsUrl()` (TS navigation), `userFindRoute()` / `userOurListingsRoute()` (`routerLink`), `USER_CREATE_<ENTITY>_URL`, `userEdit<Entity>Url(id)`. No standalone list URL constants.
2. **`admin.routes.ts`** (or `user.routes.ts`) — children under `PortalShellComponent`:
   - **Admin:** `<entity>` → table, `<entity>/create` → form, `<entity>/:id/edit` → same form.
   - **User (Plan 3):** `home`, `offer`, `find`, `our-listings` hub routes; per entity only `<entity>/create` and `<entity>/:id/edit`. List tables are embedded in hub pages — not standalone routes. Form save redirects to `userOurListingsUrl(matchingEntity)`.
3. **`admin-nav.config.ts`** / **`user-nav.config.ts`** — `NavSection` with `icon` from page icons; `route` from `app-urls.ts`.
   - **User (Plan 3):** four flat sidebar sections — Home, Find, Our listings, Offer (`NavSection.route`). Entity picking via `EntityTabsComponent` on hub pages — see `entity-tabs.mdc`, `layout.mdc`.
   - **Admin:** entity sections with all + create items (text-only).
4. **User services:** `listAll()` / `listOurs()` with company scoping (`companyId` on entity; session `companyId`); `create()` sets ownership from session.

### User hub pages (Plan 3)

| Feature folder | Route | Role |
|----------------|-------|------|
| `features/find/` | `/find?tab=` | `PageTitleComponent` + `EntityTabsComponent` + embedded `*AllTablePageComponent` (`[embedded]="true"`); no create CTA |
| `features/our-listings/` | `/our-listings?tab=` | `PageHeaderComponent` + tab-specific `PrimaryActionLink` + `EntityTabsComponent` + embedded `*OurTablePageComponent` (`[embedded]="true"`) |

Tab config: `portal/user/user-entity-tabs.config.ts` → `USER_ENTITY_TAB_CONFIG`.

Angular `path` segments in `*.routes.ts` stay relative (`vehicles`, `create`, `:id/edit`); only absolute URLs go in the domain URL files (`admin-urls.ts` for admin CRUD).

## Form page (`form/<entity>-form-page.component.ts`)

- `FormBuilder` group mirrors every field key; validators on the group, not only in the def.
- `entityId` signal from `route.snapshot.paramMap`; `isEdit = computed(() => entityId() !== null)`.
- `stepperDataReady = signal(false)` — `true` on create init; after edit `patchValue` in `queueMicrotask`.
- `formDef` computed — swap submit action for create vs edit (`*FormEditActions` pattern).
- `ngOnInit`: no `:id` → `stepperDataReady.set(true)`; with `:id` → `getById` → `patchValue` (strip `id`) → `stepperDataReady.set(true)`; load error → `navigateByUrl` list URL.
- `onSubmit`: guard `submitting`; `getRawValue() as FormModel`; create vs update; success → list URL. Do not re-validate — `FormPageComponent` already did.
- `backUrl` + `backLabelKey` — list URL and nav label for `PageBackLinkComponent` (admin: `portal.<portal>.nav.all*`; user: `userOurListingsUrl(matchingEntity)` + `portal.user.nav.our*`; same URL as post-save redirect).
- Template:

```html
<app-page-back-link [route]="backUrl" [labelKey]="backLabelKey" [form]="form" />
<app-page-title [titleKey]="pageTitleKey()" [subtitleKey]="pageSubtitleKey()" [icon]="pageIcon" />
<app-form-page
  [definition]="formDef()"
  [formGroup]="form"
  [submitDisabled]="submitting()"
  [stepperMode]="isEdit() ? 'edit' : 'create'"
  [stepperDataReady]="stepperDataReady()"
  (submit)="onSubmit()"
/>
```

- `pageTitleKey` / `pageSubtitleKey` computed — swap create vs edit `portal.<portal>.pages.*` keys; `pageIcon` from `AdminPageIcons` / `UserPageIcons` (same on list + create + edit).

- Stepper UX (free navigation, `ValidationState` pills, submit-only enforcement, mobile layout): see `forms.mdc` — do not implement in the feature page.

### User routes / cargo / storage (single-step + shared table display)

Reference: `portal/user/features/transport/`, `portal/user/features/freight/`, `portal/user/features/warehouse/`.

- **Form def:** `mode: 'single'`; origin/destination `type: 'autocomplete'` with `BIH_CITY_OPTIONS`; date fields with `minDate: 'today'` — see `forms.mdc`, `shared-constants.mdc`
- **Form page:** date validators from `shared/utils/date-input.ts`; re-validate end date when start changes; `pageIcon` from `UserPageIcons`
- **Dynamic select options:** `buildRouteForm(vehicleOptions)` / `buildStorageForm(warehouseOptions)` — clone form def, inject loaded options
- **Denormalized display on create/update:**
  - Routes: `CompanyVehicleService.getDisplay(vehicleId)` → `vehicleName`, `vehiclePlate`
  - Storage: `CompanyWarehouseService.getDisplay(warehouseId)` → `warehouseName`, `warehouseCity`; `getLabel()` → `warehouseLabel`
- **Table display widgets** (see `tables.mdc` for templates):
  - Routes + cargo: `app-route-display` (route col), `app-status-badge`, `app-date-range-display` (merged period or single needed-by)
  - Routes only: `app-vehicle-display`
  - Storage: `app-warehouse-display` (name + city), `app-status-badge`, `app-date-range-display` (availability period)
- **Portal data:** `portal/user/data/company-vehicle.service.ts`, `company-warehouse.service.ts` for cross-feature selects

## Table page (`table/<entity>-table-page.component.ts`)

- `protected readonly table = EntityTable`; `TableLoader` → `service.list(query)`.
- **Embedded mode (user Plan 3):** `embedded = input(false)`. When `true`, skip page title/header chrome; render `<app-data-table>` only. Hub pages (`find/`, `our-listings/`) compose embedded table components — see `entity-tabs.mdc`.
- **Page title row + create CTA (required when feature has create route and not embedded):** `app-page-header` with projected `app-page-title` + `app-primary-action-link` above `<app-data-table>` (outside remount `@if`). See `page-title.mdc`. Our-listings hub owns the create CTA when tables are embedded.

```html
<app-page-header>
  <app-page-title [titleKey]="pageTitleKey" [subtitleKey]="pageSubtitleKey" [icon]="pageIcon" />
  <app-primary-action-link [route]="createUrl" [labelKey]="createLabelKey" />
</app-page-header>

@if (tableMounted()) {
  <app-data-table [definition]="table" [loader]="loadEntities" (rowAction)="onRowAction($event)" />
}
```

```typescript
import { PageHeaderComponent } from '…/shared/ui/page-header/page-header.component';
import { PageTitleComponent } from '…/shared/ui/page-title/page-title.component';
import { PrimaryActionLinkComponent } from '…/shared/ui/primary-action-link/primary-action-link.component';
import { AdminPageIcons } from '…/portal/admin/admin-page-icons';
import { ADMIN_CREATE_ENTITY_URL } from '…/shared/constants/app-urls';

protected readonly pageTitleKey = 'portal.admin.pages.<entity>.title';
protected readonly pageSubtitleKey = 'portal.admin.pages.<entity>.subtitle';
protected readonly pageIcon = AdminPageIcons.<entity>;
protected readonly createUrl = ADMIN_CREATE_ENTITY_URL;
protected readonly createLabelKey = 'portal.admin.nav.createEntity';

imports: [PageHeaderComponent, PageTitleComponent, PrimaryActionLinkComponent, DataTableComponent, …],
```

- Custom enum/display cells: `tableCellKey(Table, 'column')` + `<ng-template [appTableCell]="key" let-row>` + `| translate` on label keys.
- **Status cell:** `app-status-badge` + `status` column — see `entity-status.mdc`, `tables.mdc`.
- **Route / date / vehicle / warehouse cells:** shared display components — see `tables.mdc` (do not use raw text or duplicate badge markup).
- Row actions in `onRowAction`: `edit` → `navigateByUrl(editUrl(id))`; `delete` → `ConfirmService` then `service.delete` (see `confirm.mdc`).
- After delete: remount table via `tableMounted` signal (`false` → `queueMicrotask` → `true`).

```typescript
// Delete flow (abbreviated)
this.confirmService.confirm({ titleKey, messageKey, danger: true })
  .pipe(filter(Boolean), take(1), switchMap(() => this.service.delete(id)))
  .subscribe({ next: () => this.refreshTable() });
```

## Table def (`table/<entity>.table.ts`)

- `endpoint` from `*.constants.ts` (future HTTP).
- `trackBy: 'id'`; `defaultSort`; `mobile.primary` on the main identifier column.
- **User list filters:** colocate defs in `data/*-table-filters.ts`; set `filters` + `filterStorageKey` on table def — see `table-filters.mdc`.
- `actions.items`: `edit` + `delete` (`danger: true`); handle IDs in the page, not in the def.
- Reuse form option `labelKey`s in filter `options` where enums overlap.

## i18n

Namespace: `portal.<admin|user>.features.<entity>.{form|table}.*`

- Route titles: `portal.<portal>.pages.*`
- Nav: `portal.<portal>.nav.*`
- Delete dialog: `…table.deleteConfirm.title` / `…message`; buttons use `shared.confirm.common.*`

Add keys to **both** `public/assets/en.json` and `bh.json` (see `i18n.mdc`).

## Do not

- Cross-import `portal/admin/features/**` ↔ `portal/user/features/**`.
- Hardcode app paths — use `app-urls.ts`.
- Use `window.confirm` or per-page dialog markup — use `ConfirmService`.
- Add `*.spec.ts` files.
- Rebuild table/form chrome outside `DataTableComponent` / `FormPageComponent`.
- Omit `PageBackLinkComponent` on portal create/edit form pages — see `page-title.mdc`.
- Put create CTAs inside `DataTableComponent` or `PageTitleComponent` — use `PageHeaderComponent` + `PrimaryActionLinkComponent` on the page instead.
- Render page titles inside `DataTableComponent` or `FormPageComponent` — page templates use `PageTitleComponent` (`page-title.mdc`).

